# Packing Checker – Centralized Duplicate Tag Scanning System

## Overview

Packing Checker is a centralized internal web application used to validate scanned MAC / tag codes across multiple scan stations. So we can have 1 computer be the centralized database and multiple scanners writing and reading from that singular database. 

The application prevents duplicate tags by checking scanned values against:

1. A **master CSV file** containing known existing / blocked tags  
2. A **live SQL database** containing all accepted scans during the current operation

This ensures that if one worker scans a tag successfully, another worker scanning the same tag later will be immediately flagged even if that tag does not exist in the master csv file.

So let's say that worker 1 scans tag with 12345. 1 hour later, another worker scans a tag with 12345 in another box. Even if 12345 doesn't exist in the master csv file, we will validate that every scanned mac id is unique. 

---

## Business Use Case

This system is intended for high-volume warehouse / packing / inventory operations where multiple workers scan labels simultaneously.

Example:

- 10 workers scanning tags
- 130,000 labels to process
- Need real-time duplicate prevention
- Need centralized logging and accountability

---

## Core Problem Solved

Without a centralized system:

- Workers may use stale Excel files
- Duplicate tags may slip through
- No visibility into who scanned what
- Manual reconciliation required later

With Packing Checker:

- One central source of truth
- Real-time duplicate detection
- Full scan history
- Faster operations

---

## System Architecture

```text
+-------------------+
| Master CSV File   |
| packingMac44.csv  |
+-------------------+
          |
          v
 Loads into memory on app start

+---------------------------+
| Central Windows PC        |
| Sinatra Web App           |
| SQLite / SQL Database     |
+---------------------------+
      /     /      \     \
     /     /        \     \
    v     v          v     v

[Scan Station 1]
[Scan Station 2]
[Scan Station 3]
...
[Scan Station 10]